WHO   — ATARI 7800 — an exereunesis sphere — the teardown
WHAT  — Atari's belated 2600 successor wrapped a 6502 around a smart graphics chip called MARIA that could throw far more sprites at the screen with little CPU help — and it kept the old TIA chip inside for full Atari 2600 backward compatibility. Good hardware, undone by arriving years late into Nintendo's era.
WHERE — the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored  Framework inputs: the chips; the buses; the spec; the lore  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
